docs.abstract: Kodak went bankrupt by fumbling the shift to digital images. Now, it’s betting its future on an initial coin offering to help photographers sell their work.

docs.lead_paragraph: What do you get when you cross the feverish world of cryptocurrencies and a faded industrial giant desperate for a new lease on life? The answer, provided Tuesday by Eastman Kodak, is KodakCoin.

docs.abstract: Twitter said on Friday that prohibiting a world leader from posting on the platform “would hide important information people should be able to see and debate.”
docs.snippet: Twitter said on Friday that prohibiting a world leader from posting on the platform “would hide important information people should be able to see and debate.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — For more than a year, Twitter has faced censure for allowing President Trump to use its service to say whatever he wants. And for more than a year, the company has not addressed the criticism definitively.
